HEADWORD: Merlin
<hw>Mer"lin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>merlion</ets>, F. <ets>⟦eacute⟧merillon</ets> ; cf. OHG.
<ets>smirl</ets>, G. <ets>schmerl</ets> ; prob. fr. L. <ets>merula</ets>
blackbird. Cf. <er>Merle</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A small
European falcon (<spn>Falco columbarius</spn>, syn. <spn>Falco
lithofalco</spn>, or <spn>Falco aesalon</spn>). In North America called
also <altname>pigeon hawk</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>  <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

